title: Tissue simulation
text: order perform simulation, new object class Simulation must created. step automatically builds 1000x1000-cells tissue - can host \(10^6\) cells - sets name simulation races_<date>_<hour>. binary dump simulation saved directory name simulation. custom name can provided using parameter simulation creation. Class Simulation exports print method can used get information current object print method informs : simulation name; tissue size current simulation clock; table cell types (species) simulated, empty initially. sim object exposes methods get information simulation control .
code: # Default constructor sim <- new(Simulation) # Call your simulation Test will save everything in a 'Test' folder sim <- new(Simulation, "Test") sim #> ──  rRACES   D   S   M  Test ──────────────────── ▣ A tissue [1000x1000]  ⏱ 0 ── #>     #>    =======  ===  ===  ===  ====== #>    species   λ    δ    ε   counts #>    =======  ===  ===  ===  ====== #>    =======  ===  ===  ===  ====== # Get the simulation directory, i.e., "Test" sim$get_name() #> [1] "Test"  # Get the tissue size, i.e., c(1000,1000) sim$get_tissue_size() #> [1] 1000 1000

text: order simulate evolution species need add sim. process defines evolutionary parameters species.

title: Tissue simulation
text: species RACES combination genotype epigenotype. genotype - point simulation - just name (, B etc); later stage, linked specific mutations interest. epigenotype simple binary approximation two epistates +/-, representing positive negative status. abstraction, represent active/inactive state linked promoter methylation, instance, phenotype. main important thing evolution across genotypes non-reversible, evolution among epistates potentially reversible. example, may define two genotypes B epistates +/-, obtaining 4 distinct species : + -, proxy genotype reversible +/- marker; B+ B-, proxy genotype B reversible +/- marker; species epistate, need define: growth rate \(\lambda\): rate cells duplicate inheriting epigenetic marker; death rate \(\delta\): rate cells die; epigenetic rate \(\epsilon\): rate +- -+ cells certain epistate duplicate flip epigenetic marker one progeny. example, considering genotype : one cell type + creates two cells type +; one cell type - creates two cells type -; one cell type + removed simulation; one cell type - removed simulation; one cell type + divides one type + one type -; one cell type - divides one type - one type +.
code: # we begin by adding one genotype, "A"  sim$add_genotype(name = "A",                  epigenetic_rates = c("+-" = 0.01, "-+" = 0.01),                  growth_rates = c("+" = 0.2, "-" = 0.08),                  death_rates = c("+" = 0.1, "-" = 0.01))  # updated object (counts refer to number of cells of each species) sim #> ──  rRACES   D   S   M  Test ──────────────────────── ▣ Liver [1200x900]  ⏱ 0 ── #>     #>    =======  ====  ====  ====  ====== #>    species   λ      δ    ε    counts #>    =======  ====  ====  ====  ====== #>         A-  0.08  0.01  0.01    0    #>         A+  0.20  0.10  0.01    0    #>    =======  ====  ====  ====  ======  # Get the simulation species and their rates  sim$get_species() #>   genotype epistate growth_rate death_rate switch_rate #> 1        A        -        0.08       0.01        0.01 #> 2        A        +        0.20       0.10        0.01

text: also possible take current simulation clock, simulate extra number  point, query simulation configuration find structured information (use dplyr filter query results). convenience, getters accept parameters subset tissue. Note rRACES method select specific cells tissue. example, can randomly select one cell genotype
code: # Get the simulation clock sim$get_clock() #> [1] 66.38608  # Run the simulation for other 15 time units sim$run_up_to_time(sim$get_clock() + 15)  # Get again the simulation clock sim$get_clock() #> [1] 81.38625 plot_tissue(sim) # load dplyr to use %>% require(dplyr)  # Get the cells in the tissue at current simulation time sim$get_cells() %>% head() #>   cell_id genotype epistate position_x position_y #> 1   69985        A        +        408        487 #> 2   74108        A        +        408        497 #> 3   51495        A        -        409        487 #> 4   85055        A        +        409        497 #> 5   73287        A        +        409        498 #> 6   46156        A        -        410        485  # Get the cells in the tissue rectangular sample having # [500,500] and [505,505] as lower and upper corners, respectively sim$get_cells(c(500, 500), c(505, 505))  %>% head() #>   cell_id genotype epistate position_x position_y #> 1   72689        A        +        500        500 #> 2   54473        A        -        500        501 #> 3   48193        A        -        500        502 #> 4   74612        A        +        500        503 #> 5   84434        A        +        500        504 #> 6   83999        A        +        500        505  # Get the cells in the tissue having epigenetic state "-" sim$get_cells(c("A", "B"), c("-")) %>% head() #>   cell_id genotype epistate position_x position_y #> 1   51495        A        -        409        487 #> 2   46156        A        -        410        485 #> 3   51557        A        -        410        504 #> 4   59394        A        -        411        488 #> 5   91066        A        -        411        514 #> 6   51163        A        -        412        501  # Get the cells in the tissue having epigenetic state "-" and, # at the same time, belonging to rectangular sample bounded by # [500,500] and [505,505] as lower and upper corners, respectively sim$get_cells(c(500, 500), c(505, 505), c("A", "B"), c("-"))  %>% head() #>   cell_id genotype epistate position_x position_y #> 1   54473        A        -        500        501 #> 2   48193        A        -        500        502 #> 3   86441        A        -        501        500 #> 4   78265        A        -        501        501 #> 5   86442        A        -        501        502 #> 6   79073        A        -        504        500 # Stochastic sampling from the whole tissue sim$choose_cell_in("A") #>   cell_id genotype epistate position_x position_y #> 1   68158        A        +        481        575  # Calling it again may result in a different cell sim$choose_cell_in("A") #>   cell_id genotype epistate position_x position_y #> 1   68178        A        +        569        529  # Constrain sampling in the tissue rectangular selection [500,550]x[350,450]  sim$choose_cell_in("A",  c(500, 350), c(550, 450)) #>   cell_id genotype epistate position_x position_y #> 1   87012        A        +        502        426

title: Tissue simulation
text: far, simulation contains single genotype . general, might want consider case multiple clones different genotypes. time-point simulation rRACES allows insert new genotype. add new genotype B – therefore new species B+ B- - descending ,need : locate one cell genotype tissue, inject new clone; add specifics genotype B (via add_genotype, ) implement change cell genotype cell genotype B; locate random cell add genotype inject cell, simulate little bit.    , point simulation, like generate new genotype C one cells genotype rectangle \([450,500]\times [550, 600]\), need : randomly select one cell among laying \([450,500]\times [550, 600]\) calling choose_cell_in setup new genotype C call mutate_progeny method
code: # Sampled cell cell <- sim$choose_cell_in("A") cell #>   cell_id genotype epistate position_x position_y #> 1   68158        A        +        481        575  # Add genotype sim$add_genotype(name = "B",                  epigenetic_rates = c("+-" = 0.05, "-+" = 0.05),                  growth_rates = c("+" = 0.3, "-" = 0.3),                  death_rates = c("+" = 0.05, "-" = 0.1)) sim$mutate_progeny(cell, "B")  # Generated event A -> B either in + or - species sim$get_counts() #>   genotype epistate counts #> 1        A        -   5702 #> 2        A        +  20078 #> 3        B        -      0 #> 4        B        +      1  # Simulation sim$run_up_to_size("B+", 1000) plot_state(sim) plot_tissue(sim) # Facet on species via ggplot library(ggplot2)  plot_tissue(sim) + facet_wrap(~species) cell <- sim$choose_cell_in("A",  c(450, 550), c(500, 600))  sim$add_genotype(name = "C",                  epigenetic_rates = c("+-" = 0.1, "-+" = 0.1),                  growth_rates = c("+" = 0.2, "-" = 0.4),                  death_rates = c("+" = 0.1, "-" = 0.01))  sim$mutate_progeny(cell, "C")  # Everything should be correct sim$get_cell(cell$position_x, cell$position_y) #>   cell_id genotype epistate position_x position_y #> 1 1221399        C        -        487        566  sim$run_up_to_time(sim$get_clock() + 10) plot_state(sim) plot_tissue(sim)

title: Tissue simulation
text: convenient sometimes plot time series simulation, reporting species firing counts time. Since rRACES programmable, immediate make -loop algorithm collect simulation data time. However, required end run_to_* methods, RACES stores data number species cells event firings. rRACES makes data accessible via specific getters. time-series can plot using plot_timeseries  rRACES offers possibility performing coarse-grained storing history, independently actual data stored evaluation run_to_* method. , can set Simulation property history_delta (default \(1\)). default, history_delta set \(0\), can set real value \(d\) dump simulation statistics every \(d\) time units. time-series can plot using plot_timeseries, similary can plot Muller plot using ggmuller.
code: # The firings sim$get_firing_history() %>% head() #>    event genotype epistate fired     time #> 1  death        A        -     6 45.00946 #> 2 growth        A        -    72 45.00946 #> 3 switch        A        -     9 45.00946 #> 4  death        A        +   344 45.00946 #> 5 growth        A        +   874 45.00946 #> 6 switch        A        +    39 45.00946  # For example, total number of the deaths on `B+` at the end of the  # previous calls of the `run_to_*` methods sim$get_firing_history() %>%   filter(event == "death", genotype == "B", epistate == "-")  #>   event genotype epistate fired      time #> 1 death        B        -     0  45.00946 #> 2 death        B        -     0  66.38608 #> 3 death        B        -     0  81.38625 #> 4 death        B        -   186 106.53202 #> 5 death        B        -  1740 116.53203  # The counts sim$get_count_history() %>% head() #>   genotype epistate count     time #> 1        A        -    96 45.00946 #> 2        A        +   500 45.00946 #> 3        B        -     0 45.00946 #> 4        B        +     0 45.00946 #> 5        C        -     0 45.00946 #> 6        C        +     0 45.00946 # Time-series plot plot_timeseries(sim) # Example time-series on a new simulation sim_ts <- new(Simulation)  # every time-point sim_ts$history_delta = 1  sim_ts$add_genotype(name = "A",                     growth_rates = 0.08,                     death_rates = 0.01)  sim_ts$place_cell("A", 500, 500)  sim_ts$run_up_to_size("A", 4000) # Time-series plot plot_timeseries(sim_ts) # Muller plot plot_muller(sim_ts)

title: Tissue simulation
text: species death rate greater 0 can become extinct soon appears due premature death progenitor cell. phenomenon called drift, occurs spontaneously nature. makes difficult simulate confident species model. Users can avoid drift setting death activation level. value minimum number cells enables cell death species. cell species \(S\) can die $S$ reached death activation level least simulation. threshold holds species set 1 default. However, can risen much want avoid drift
code: sim$death_activation_level #> [1] 1 sim$death_activation_level <- 50

title: Simulates the cell evolution on a tissue — Simulation
text: add_genotype Adds genotype species Parameter: genotype - genotype name. Parameter: epigenetic_rates - epigenetic rates genotype species (optional). Parameter: growth_rates - duplication rates genotype species. Parameter: death_rates - death rates genotype species. choose_cell_in Chooses one cell genotype Parameter: genotype - genotype cell choose. Parameter: lower_corner - lower left corner rectangular selection (optional). Parameter: upper_corner - upper right corner rectangular selection (optional). Returns: list reporting "cell_id", "genotype", "epistate", "position_x",    "position_y" choosen cell. death_activation_level number cells activates cell death species get_added_cells Gets cells manually added simulation Returns: data frame reporting "genotype", "epistate", "position_x",         "position_y", "time" cells manually added          simulation. get_cell Gets one tissue cells Parameter: x - position aimed cell x axis. Parameter: y - position aimed cell y axis. Returns: data frame reporting "cell_id", "genotype", "epistate", "position_x",    "position_y" aimed cell. get_cells Gets tissue cells Parameter: lower_corner - lower-left corner selection frame (optional). Parameter: upper_corner - upper-right corner selection frame (optional). Parameter: genotype_filter - vector --selected genotype names (optional). Parameter: epigenetic_filter - vector --selected epigenetic states (optional). Returns: data frame reporting "cell_id", "genotype", "epistate", "position_x",    "position_y" cells satisfying provided filters laying     input frame. get_clock Gets simulated time Returns: time simulated simulation. get_count_history Gets history number cells per species Returns: data frame reporting "genotype", "epistate", "counts",     "time" species sampled time. get_counts Counts number cells Returns: data frame reporting "genotype", "epistate", "counts"      species simulation. get_firing_history Gets history number fired events Returns: data frame reporting "event", "genotype", "epistate", "fired",       "time" event type, species, sampled time. get_firings Gets number fired events Returns: data frame reporting "event", "genotype", "epistate", "fired"     event type species. get_name Gets simulation name Returns: simulation name, corresponds name directory          simulation saving progresses. get_lineage_graph Gets simulation lineage graph Returns: data frame reporting "ancestor", "progeny", "first_occurrence"          species--species transition. get_rates Gets rates species Parameter: species - species whose rates aimed. Returns: list species names. get_species Gets species Returns: data frame describing registered species. get_tissue_name Gets tissue name Returns: name simulated tissue. get_tissue_size Gets size simulated tissue Returns: vector `c(x_size, y_size)` simulated tissue. mutate_progeny Generate mutated offspring Parameter: cell_position - position cell whose offspring mutate. Parameter: mutated_genotype - genotype mutated cell. Parameter: x - position cell whose progeny mutate x axis. Parameter: y - position cell whose progeny mutate y axis. Parameter: mutated_genotype - genotype mutated cell. place_cell Place one cell tissue Parameter: species - name new cell species. Parameter: x - position x axis cell. Parameter: y - position y axis cell. schedule_genotype_mutation Schedules genotype mutation Parameter: src - name genotype mutation occurs. Parameter: dest - name genotype mutation leads. Parameter: time - simulated time mutation occurs. run_up_to_event Simulates cell evolution Parameter: event - considered event type, .e., "growth", "death", "switch". Parameter: species - species whose event number considered. Parameter: num_of_events - threshold event number. run_up_to_size Simulates cell evolution Parameter: species - species whose number cells considered. Parameter: num_of_cells - threshold cell number. run_up_to_time Simulates cell evolution Parameter: time - final simulation time. update_rates Updates rates species Parameter: species - species whose rates must updated. Parameter: rates - list rates updated. Returns: vector species names. update_tissue Updates tissue name size Parameter: name - new name tissue (optional). Parameter: width - width new tissue. Parameter: height - height new tissue.

code: # create a simulation having name "recover_simulation_test" sim <- new(Simulation, "recover_simulation_test")  # add the species of "A" sim$add_genotype("A",                  epigenetic_rates=c("+-" = 0.01, "-+"=0.01),                  growth_rates = c("+"=0.1, "-"=0.01),                  death_rates = c("+"=0.05, "-"=0.005))  # place a cell in the tissue sim$place_cell("A+", 500, 500)  # simulate up to time 50 sim$run_up_to_time(50)  # show the simulation sim #> ──  rRACES   D   S   M  recover_simulation_test ──────────────────────────────── #>     #>    =======  ====  =====  ====  ====== #>    species   λ       δ    ε    counts #>    =======  ====  =====  ====  ====== #>         A-  0.01  0.005  0.01    4    #>         A+  0.10  0.050  0.01    22   #>    =======  ====  =====  ====  ======  # remove the object sim from the environment rm(list=c("sim"))  # the object pointed by sim does not exist any more exists("sim") #> [1] FALSE  # recover the simulation from the directory "recover_simulation_test" sim <- recover_simulation("recover_simulation_test")  sim #> ──  rRACES   D   S   M  recover_simulation_test ──────────────────────────────── #>     #>    =======  ====  =====  ====  ====== #>    species   λ       δ    ε    counts #>    =======  ====  =====  ====  ====== #>         A-  0.01  0.005  0.01    4    #>         A+  0.10  0.050  0.01    22   #>    =======  ====  =====  ====  ======
